comments: Gobert (MIN) establishes himself in Hart's (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
McDaniels (MIN) initiates contact with Randle's (NYK) arm as he goes behind his back and affects his ability to continue his dribble.
After the ball becomes loose, Randle (NYK) grabs McDaniels' (MIN) arm and lower body affecting his ability to pursue the ball.
Brunson (NYK) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Conley (MIN) legally contests Quickley's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Gobert (MIN) turns to roll and incidental contact occurs with Brunson (NYK) as Brunson (NYK) attempts to go under the pick.

Replay review of the personal foul called on Anderson (MIN) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Anderson (MIN) reaches in and makes contact with the ball that dislodges it away from Quickley (NYK) during his drive. The arm contact that occurs after the ball is dislodged is incidental.
Randle (NYK) avoids making contact with Conley's (MIN) arm when he loses control of the ball. After the ball becomes loose, Conley and Quickley (NYK) engage in incidental contact.
Prince (MIN) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Randle's (NYK) driving shot attempt.
McDaniels (MIN) uses his off-arm to clear space from Brunson (NYK), which affects Brunson's (NYK) ability to defend during the drive.
Brunson (NYK) legally contests McDaniels' (MIN) jump shot attempt.
Anderson (MIN) avoids making contact to the arm and cleanly dislodges the ball from Randle (NYK) during the rebound attempt.
Randle (NYK) jumps alongside Prince (MIN) and marginal body contact occurs during Prince's (MIN) upward shooting motion.
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
McDaniels (MIN) legally contests Randle's (NYK) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Hartenstein (NYK) deflects the ball out of bounds.
